modules.description: This module offers operations for managing associative containers with string keys and arbitrary values, including insertion, deletion, lookup, and transformation. It supports advanced manipulations like filtering, merging, predicate-based queries, and value transformations, enabling efficient data processing in scenarios such as configuration management or symbolic computation. Specific use cases involve extracting extremal elements, splitting maps, or applying functions to key-value pairs for domain-specific data manipulation.

Generates JSX syntax for ReasonReact by transforming OCaml code during compilation. Processes OCaml modules and expressions, inserting React component definitions and element syntax. Enables writing React components in OCaml with a syntax similar to JSX in JavaScript.

Provides operations for manipulating associative containers with string keys and arbitrary values, supporting insertion, deletion, lookup, and transformation. It enables advanced data processing through filtering, merging, and predicate-based queries, along with key-value pair transformations. Users can extract extremal elements, split maps, or apply custom functions for domain-specific tasks. Examples include configuring systems, managing symbolic data, and restructuring key-value collections.
